  this  act  shall  act  as  a  deterrent  for  all those  employers  engaging  children  and  also  the  parents  who  force  their  own children  to  work  at  a  tender  age    however  allowing  children  below  14  years  of age  to  work  only  in  family  enterprises  may  dilute  the  very  spirit  of  the  bill    i request  the  government to look  into  this  aspect   it is  a  welcome  feature that  the offences  of  employing  children  in  contravention  of  the  law  have  been  made cognizable which would act as a deterrent  the whole intention of the government in  bringing  this  legislation  is  appreciated  but  much  more  has  to  be  done  for children    